Explanation
What is a server?

A server is a computer that provides services, resources, or data to other computers over a network.

What is the role of the domain name?

The domain name foobar.com provides a human-readable address that users can type into a browser instead of remembering an IP address.

What type of DNS record is www in www.foobar.com?

www is typically an A record, which maps a hostname to an IPv4 address (8.8.8.8).

What is the role of the web server (Nginx)?

The web server receives HTTP/HTTPS requests from clients and serves static content or forwards requests to the application server.

What is the role of the application server?

The application server executes the application logic and generates dynamic content.

What is the role of the database (MySQL)?

The database stores and retrieves application data such as users, posts, products, and settings.

What is the server using to communicate with the user's computer?

The server communicates with the client using the TCP/IP protocol suite, typically through HTTP or HTTPS.

Issues with this Infrastructure
1. SPOF (Single Point of Failure)

The entire website depends on one server. If that server fails, the website becomes unavailable.

2. Downtime during maintenance

Deploying new code, restarting services, or performing updates may temporarily take the website offline.

3. Cannot scale

A single server has limited CPU, memory, disk, and network resources. High traffic can overwhelm it, causing slow responses or outages.

Acronyms
LAMP: Linux, Apache, MySQL, PHP (or Perl/Python)
SPOF: Single Point Of Failure
QPS: Queries Per Second
